race.description: Ladbrokes Racing Extras In Multi Hcp (56)
race.comment: MUMMSIE (11) has been out of the placings in two runs since a break, the latest when ninth, beaten 9 lengths, over 1700m at Warrnambool after she was in contention on the bend. Has never been out of the placings at the third run in, though, and looks set to find best form. SHE FLYS (12) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1500m at Ballarat, beaten 3.5 lengths into sixth. Finds an easier assignment and can find winning form. SUMMER NIGHT (6) progressed nicely last time out to finish just 1.3 lengths from the winner in second over 1400m at Ballarat after being in contention on the turn. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. WARAKURNA (7) has not won for a long while. Last raced on October 6 when beaten 5.5 lengths into eighth at Ballarat over 1400m. Likely improver who should be about the money.
